# Optional. Compose can read a `.env` here for ${API_PORT} / ${UI_PORT}. Postgres maps host **5454** in docker-compose.yml.
# If you only maintain api/.env, run Compose with:
#   docker compose --env-file ./api/.env -f docker-compose.yml [-f docker-compose.prod.yml] up -d
#
# Example (duplicate of api/.env ports if you prefer a root .env):
# API_PORT=3003
# UI_PORT=3002
# DB_PORT=5454
